(-1)!! = 1
n
k\in \mathbb{Z}
n = 2k-1
n!! = (2k-1)!! = \dfrac{(2k)!}{2^k k!}.
\text{At}\;k = 0,\;\;\;(2\cdot 0 - 1)!! = (-1)!! = \frac{0!}{2^0 0!} = \frac{1}{1\cdot 1} = 1.
n = 2k\,
k \in \mathbb{Z}
n\,!\,! = (2k)\,!\,! \;= \;2^k\, k\,!
k
k \ge 1
n
 n!!=\frac{(n+2)!!}{n+2} 
 (-1)!!=\frac{(-1+2)!!}{(-1+2)}=\frac{1!!}{1}=1. 
